SXTPS is a new events collective creating space for the intersections of Black and Brown rainbow mafia nightlife. We are love letter to the kids of the underground. A space for those who love. An ode to the artists that paved the way. A journey into self thru music, entertainment, and intimacy. A response to the white elite. A chance for community.

Stay tuned for announcements for our first public event, coming soon!

I’m very excited to finally be able to publicly announce the launch of my new arts and events collective, SXTPS.

I am partnering with @iamgarylopez to build a new project in curating space for Black and Brown Queer people, thru music, entertainment, art, and intimacy. 

This weekend, we are celebrating our launch with a private pool party, to help spread the word, and captivate our guest with feel good beats, connection, and love.

Stay tuned for the announcement of our first public party, coming soon! In the meantime, follow up for all updates over at @sxtps.exe!

My entire adult life, I’ve wanted a dog. This year, I decided to adopt, commemorating my upcoming 30th birthday. I welcomed this one into the family about a month and a half ago. He’s a rescue from @laanimalservices, and has to be one of the sweetest pieces of shit I’ve ever met.

It’s been a hell of a roller coaster learning each other, and reorganizing life to fit in such a huge responsibility.

Motherhood is hard. But I’m already loving it.

The time has come. SXTPS initializes this fall. 🔋

SXTPS is a passion project thru which I tell the story of my own self discovery through my experience as an artist in underground nightlife. Not only is this a party, it’s a love letter to the people and the music that have inspired me along the way. 

Bringing SXTPS to life is curating an experience that gives room for the sounds, the emotions, the rhythms, and the spirit to finally be free.

It will be a celebration for all of us. We need it. 🙌🏽

I’m still on such a high from this weekend. I can’t believe how y’all showed out for the first @sxtps.exe party. It is such an honor to have seen it be so well received by so many people that I love and respect. 

I cannot wait to bring more.

Thank you to my sister-homie-bestie and business partner, @iamgarylopez, for believing in my vision and joining me in this journey. 

Thanks to my brother @iammontechristo for bringing the fucking heat in that opening set, and for working with me in curating the vibe. Thank you for being a pioneer in this scene; your inspiration has fueled me in so many ways. Our talks have saved me from quitting. Your impact is forever appreciated.

Thank you to everyone who came out and made this event such a success. This is only the first stop on a long road ahead. I can’t wait to show y’all what we’re cooking up. 

Until then, check out this new photo album on the website SXTPS.com by @davidelaffe.
